NGUYỄN THỊ BẢO TRÂN is an Intern Software Engineer with a strong academic foundation, currently pursuing both a Bachelor's in Software Engineering and a Master's in Computer Science, demonstrating a GPA of 8.01. Their core expertise spans **IoT Architecture**, **Mobile App Development** (Android), **Web Development** (E-commerce), and **Desktop App Development**, underpinned by a solid understanding of **System Design** and certified proficiency in **Agile** and **Scrum** methodologies. Through academic projects, they have engineered a comprehensive **IoT system** for smart lock management, integrating smartphone controls, temporary passcodes, firmware updates, and abnormal activity alerts using C++, C, Dart, Swift, HTML, and CMake. Further experience includes developing **Android applications** for online movie ticket booking and student information management with Java and Kotlin, featuring functionalities like seat selection, payment processing, and CRUD operations. They also built an **e-commerce website** utilizing PHP, JavaScript, HTML, and Hack, complete with product management, shopping cart, and an administrative panel, alongside a **Work Management system** in C# and TSQL for employee and task tracking.
Technically, NGUYỄN THỊ BẢO TRÂN is proficient across a wide array of **programming languages**, including C, C++, C#, Dart, Hack, HTML, Java, JavaScript, Kotlin, PHP, Python, Swift, and XML. They possess hands-on experience with **database management systems** such as MySQL, NoSQL, SQL, and TSQL, and are adept with **development tools** like CMake and Git. Their domain knowledge encompasses **IoT systems**, **e-commerce platforms**, **mobile application development**, and **desktop application solutions**, demonstrating practical application of **Agile** and **Scrum** principles. With an Intermediate (B2) English proficiency, they are well-equipped for collaborative technical environments.